I"	
<p>In this example, $s_1$ is the initial position and $s_3$ is the final position.</p>

<figure style="text-align: center;">
  <img src="/images/content/phys1/phys1-3.1.2.png" alt="my alt text" width="500px" />
  <figcaption><em>
</em></figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Hence,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\Delta \vv{s} &amp;= s_f-s_i \\
	&amp;= s_3-s_1 \\
	&amp;= -2-5 \\
	&amp;= -7 \text{ units to the $\tcBal{positive}$ direction $\quad$ or} \\
	&amp;= 7  \text{ units to the $\tcBal{negative}$ direction}	\tagans
\end{align*}\]

